1881 
1882 /*
1883  * ======== System_printfExtend__I ========
1884  * This function processes optional extended formats of printf.
1885  *
1886  * It returns the number of characters added to the result.
1887  *
1888  * Precision (maximum string length) is not supported for %$S.
1889  *
1890  * Right-justified (which is default) minimum width is not supported
1891  * for %$L, %$S, or %$F.
1892  */
1893 xdc_Int xdc_runtime_System_printfExtend__I(xdc_Char **pbuf, xdc_CString *pfmt,
1894  xdc_VaList *pva, xdc_runtime_System_ParseData *parse)
1895 {
1896  xdc_CString fmt = *pfmt;
1897  xdc_Int res;
1898  xdc_Char c;
1899  xdc_Bool found = FALSE;
1900 
1901  /*
1902  * Create a local variable 'va' to ensure that the dereference of
1903  * pva only occurs once.
1904  */
1905  va_list va = *pva;
1906 
1907  res = 0;
1908 
1909  c = *fmt++;
1910  *pfmt = *pfmt + 1;
1911 
1912 
1913  if (c == '$') {
1914  c = *fmt++;
1915  *pfmt = *pfmt + 1;
1916 
1917  if (c == 'L') {
1918  xdc_runtime_Types_Label *lab = parse->aFlag ?
1919  (xdc_runtime_Types_Label *)xdc_iargToPtr(va_arg(va, xdc_IArg)) :
1920  (xdc_runtime_Types_Label *)va_arg(va, void *);
1921 
1922  /*
1923  * Call Text_putLab to write out the label, taking the precision
1924  * into account.
1925  */
1926  res = xdc_runtime_Text_putLab(lab, pbuf, parse->precis);
1927 
1928  /*
1929  * Set the length to 0 to indicate to 'doPrint' that nothing should
1930  * be copied from parse.ptr.
1931  */
1932  parse->len = 0;
1933 
1934  /* Update the minimum width field. */
1935  parse->width -= res;
1936 
1937  found = TRUE;
1938  }
1939 
1940  if (c == 'F') {
1941  xdc_runtime_Types_Site site;
1942 
1943  /* Retrieve the file name string from the argument list */
1944  site.file = parse->aFlag ? (xdc_Char *) xdc_iargToPtr(va_arg(va, xdc_IArg)) :
1945  (xdc_Char *) va_arg(va, xdc_Char *);
1946 
1947  /* Retrieve the line number from the argument list. */
1948  site.line = parse->aFlag ? (xdc_Int) va_arg(va, xdc_IArg) :
1949  (xdc_Int) va_arg(va, xdc_Int);
1950 
1951  /*
1952  * Omit the 'mod' field, set it to 0.
1953  * '0' is a safe sentinel value - the IDs for named modules are
1954  * 0x8000 and higher, and the IDs for unnamed modules go from 0x1
1955  * to 0x7fff.
1956  */
1957  site.mod = 0;
1958 
1959  /*
1960  * Call putSite to format the file and line number.
1961  * If a precision was specified, it will be used as the maximum
1962  * string lengrth.
1963  */
1964  res = xdc_runtime_Text_putSite(&site, pbuf, parse->precis);
1965 
1966  /*
1967  * Set the length to 0 to indicate to 'doPrint' that nothing should
1968  * be copied from parse.ptr.
1969  */
1970  parse->len = 0;
1971 
1972  /* Update the minimum width field */
1973  parse->width -= res;
1974 
1975  found = TRUE;
1976  }
1977 
1978  if (c == 'S') {
1979  /* Retrieve the format string from the argument list */
1980  parse->ptr = parse->aFlag ?
1981  (xdc_Char *) xdc_iargToPtr(va_arg(va, xdc_IArg)) :
1982  (xdc_Char *) va_arg(va, xdc_Char *);
1983 
1984  /* Update pva before passing it to doPrint. */
1985  *pva = va;
1986 
1987  /* Perform the recursive format. System_doPrint does not advance
1988  * the buffer pointer, so it has to be done explicitly.
1989  */
1990  res = xdc_runtime_System_doPrint__I(*pbuf, parse->precis,
1991  parse->ptr, pva, parse->aFlag);
1992 
1993  if (*pbuf) {
1994  *pbuf += res;
1995  }
1996 
1997  /* Update the temporary variable with any changes to *pva */
1998  va = *pva;
1999 
2000  /*
2001  * Set the length to 0 to indicate to 'doPrint' that nothing should
2002  * be copied from parse.ptr
2003  */
2004  parse->len = 0;
2005 
2006  /* Update the minimum width field */
2007  parse->width -= res;
2008 
2009  /* Indicate that we were able to interpret the specifier */
2010  found = TRUE;
2011  }
2012 
2013  }
2014 
2015  if (c == 'f') {
2016  /* support arguments _after_ optional float support */
2017  if (parse->aFlag) {
2018  (void)va_arg(va, xdc_IArg);
2019  }
2020  else {
2021  (void)va_arg(va, double);
2022  }
2023  }
2024 
2025  if (found == FALSE) {
2026  /* other character (like %) copy to output */
2027  *(parse->ptr) = c;
2028  parse->len = 1;
2029  }
2030 
2031  /*
2032  * Before returning, we must update the value of pva. We use a label here
2033  * so that all return points will go through this update.
2034  * The 'goto end' is here to ensure that there is always a reference to the
2035  * label (to avoid the compiler complaining).
2036  */
2037  goto end;
2038 end:
2039  *pva = va;
2040  return (res);
2041 }

2440 
2441 /*
2442  * Header is a union to make sure that the size is a power of 2.
2443  *
2444  * On the MSP430 small model (MSP430X), size_t is 2 bytes, which makes
2445  * the size of this struct 6 bytes.
2446  */
2447 typedef union Header {
2448  struct {
2449  Ptr actualBuf;
2450  SizeT size;
2451  } header;
2452  UArg pad[2]; /* 4 words on 28L, 8 bytes on most others */
2453 } Header;
2454 
2455 /*
2456  * ======== malloc ========
2457  */
2458 Void ATTRIBUTE *malloc(SizeT size)
2459 {
2460  Header *packet;
2461  xdc_runtime_Error_Block eb;
2462 
2463  xdc_runtime_Error_init(&eb);
2464 
2465  if (size == 0) {
2466  return (NULL);
2467  }
2468 
2469  packet = (Header *)xdc_runtime_Memory_alloc(NULL,
2470  (SizeT)(size + sizeof(Header)), 0, &eb);
2471 
2472  if (packet == NULL) {
2473  return (NULL);
2474  }
2475 
2476  packet->header.actualBuf = (Ptr)packet;
2477  packet->header.size = size + sizeof(Header);
2478 
2479  return (packet + 1);
2480 }
2481 
2482 /*
2483  * ======== memalign ========
2484  * mirrors the memalign() function from the TI run-time library
2485  */
2486 Void ATTRIBUTE *memalign(SizeT alignment, SizeT size)
2487 {
2488  Header *packet;
2489  Void *tmp;
2490  xdc_runtime_Error_Block eb;
2491 
2492  xdc_runtime_Error_init(&eb);
2493 
2494  if (alignment < sizeof(Header)) {
2495  alignment = sizeof(Header);
2496  }
2497 
2498  /*
2499  * return NULL if size is 0, or alignment is not a power of 2
2500  */
2501  if (size == 0 || (alignment & (alignment - 1))) {
2502  return (NULL);
2503  }
2504 
2505  /*
2506  * Allocate 'align + size' so that we have room for the 'packet'
2507  * and can return an aligned buffer.
2508  */
2509  tmp = xdc_runtime_Memory_alloc(NULL, alignment + size, alignment, &eb);
2510 
2511  if (tmp == NULL) {
2512  return (NULL);
2513  }
2514 
2515  packet = (Header *)((char *)tmp + alignment - sizeof(Header));
2516 
2517  packet->header.actualBuf = tmp;
2518  packet->header.size = size + sizeof(Header);
2519 
2520  return (packet + 1);
2521 }
2522 
2523 /*
2524  * ======== calloc ========
2525  */
2526 Void ATTRIBUTE *calloc(SizeT nmemb, SizeT size)
2527 {
2528  SizeT nbytes;
2529  Ptr retval;
2530 
2531  nbytes = nmemb * size;
2532 
2533  /* return NULL if there's an overflow */
2534  if (nmemb && size != (nbytes / nmemb)) {
2535  return (NULL);
2536  }
2537 
2538  retval = malloc(nbytes);
2539  if (retval != NULL) {
2540  (Void)memset(retval, (Int)'\0', nbytes);
2541  }
2542 
2543  return (retval);
2544 }
2545 
2546 /*
2547  * ======== free ========
2548  */
2549 Void ATTRIBUTE free(Void *ptr)
2550 {
2551  Header *packet;
2552 
2553  if (ptr != NULL) {
2554  packet = ((Header *)ptr) - 1;
2555 
2556  xdc_runtime_Memory_free(NULL, (Ptr)packet->header.actualBuf,
2557  (packet->header.size +
2558  ((char*)packet - (char*)packet->header.actualBuf)));
2559  }
2560 }
2561 
2562 /*
2563  * ======== realloc ========
2564  */
2565 Void ATTRIBUTE *realloc(Void *ptr, SizeT size)
2566 {
2567  Ptr retval;
2568  Header *packet;
2569  SizeT oldSize;
2570 
2571  if (ptr == NULL) {
2572  retval = malloc(size);
2573  }
2574  else if (size == 0) {
2575  free(ptr);
2576  retval = NULL;
2577  }
2578  else {
2579  packet = (Header *)ptr - 1;
2580  retval = malloc(size);
2581  if (retval != NULL) {
2582  oldSize = packet->header.size - sizeof(Header);
2583  (Void)memcpy(retval, ptr, (size < oldSize) ? size : oldSize);
2584  free(ptr);
2585  }
2586  }
2587 
2588  return (retval);
2589 }

2595  */
2596 Void ATTRIBUTE *_malloc_r(struct _reent *rptr, SizeT size)
2597 {
2598  return malloc(size);
2599 }
